            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hey everyone, I'm back with some news. I tried out the bug on a different computer. It has the same version of Windows, but the important thing is that it's a different computer and that it's a computer that still has a relatively fresh install of Windows on it. Actually, the whole computer is pretty fresh. Welp, once I got access to it, I checked out the 2 ways to open NVim I talked about before, and none of them had the bug.\n\nNow that's interesting, and I'm wondering where to take this next. I still have a bunch of computers to test out on left with different specs, so we'll see how it exactly pans out, I'll test it out when I get access to them.\n\nAgain, I'm requesting for someone to test out the bug on their own machine, try to replicate it with the two methods, but also for someone to read this, and third, I want to talk with someone who's pretty knowledgeable at NVim, maybe that'll help figure some stuff out.\n\nMaybe there's some NVim option that could break the intended behaviour or there's something, etc.\n\nI've done some more observations, but they didn't yield any results. One of them, for example, was comparing the window settings of a separate NVim terminal and of a parent-instantiated NVim terminal. Obviously, there were some differences, but none stood out to seem to be the cause of the issue.\n\nAnyways, have a nice day, thanks for reading and replying in advance. Imma go.",
